"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-07-olympic-champion-apologises-dad-savage-comment-winning-gold-21380203\", \"text\": \"OlympicchampionJessica Foxhas apologised to her dad after putting him down with a 'really mean' dig after winning gold inParis.  The 30-year-old slalom canoeist 'completed' the Olympics by winning gold in the K1 event in Paris, having won silver at London 2012 and bronze at the previous two Games.  There was more reason for the Fox family to celebrate in Paris as Jessica's sister Noemie\\u00a0also won gold in the first ever women's slalom kayak cross event.  It's hardly surprising that Jessica and Noemie\\u00a0have developed into world-class, Olympic-winning athletes as both their parents were also stars of the canoeing world.  Mum Myriam Fox-Jerusalmi competed at the international level from 1979 to 1996 and won bronze in the K1 at the Atlanta Olympics in 1996.  The French star also won ten medals at the ICF Canoe Slalom World Championships and the World Cup title three consecutive times between 1989 and 1991.  Dad Richard, meanwhile, competed for Great Britain for the best part of two decades, winning ten gold medals at the World Championships.  But Richard is the only family member without an Olympic medal, having finished fourth and narrowly missing out on silverware in the 1992 Olympics in Barcelona.  Speaking to Australian TV following sister Noemie's\\u00a0Olympic gold, Jessica poked fun at her dad's misfortunate, saying: 'It means that poor dad is the only one without an Olympic medal!  'What a moment for our family. What a moment for these games.'  Almost 24 hours after the dig, Jessica issued a public apology to her dad, insisting he should proud of his 'great resume' despite his Olympic disappointment.  'I was pretty savage in my interview, and I realised after that was really mean,' she told Australian broadcaster Channel Nine.  'Sorry, Dad. You have a great resume, 10-time\\u00a0world\\u00a0champion, amazing! We have got four gold medals in the family, so there is one for everyone.'  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Ireland's Olympic hero Daniel Wiffen 'rushed to hospital' before closing ceremony  ArrowMORE:Six new sports revealed for next Olympics as one gets scrapped  ArrowMORE:Map reveals nuclear fallout that would happen if Europe's biggest plant explodes  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"